(29, 357, 'Blang Kolam Waterfall', 'blang-kolam-waterfall', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Blang Kolam Waterfall</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Blang Kolam Waterfall is situated in a shady forest in North Aceh Regency with an altitude of about 75 meters. It is in cool area with exquisite nature. For those who willingly experience to have a chill nuance of the waterfall, tourists can bathe beneath the waterfall or just relax enjoying its natura athmosphere. This place is very suitable for family recreation.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">For those who love the adrenaline rush this waterfall is a good destination to visit. To reach the waterfall, all tourists must to down dozens of stairs due to the location of the waterfall is under the deep slopes down. There is a large 4 meters rock in front of the waterfall, and it commonly used to be climbed and jumped into the pool. On weekends, there will be many who people lined up to jump out of this spot. For those who can not swim, it is suggested to play around the water from the top of the rock, to feel the sensation of fish inside the water.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">In addition, the facilities and amenities are well-equipped. All visitors can easily find a prayer room and restroom in this area. There are many food and beverage vendors at the waterfall site, it is good for meals or just resting while enjoying the shady nuance over the forest.There are also many electricity powers that can be used to make your holiday more comfortable and enjoyable while the battery of your devices such camera or mobile phone are low. The security guards are also secured the area well. Furthermore, the parking area is safe.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Additional Information</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Location                    : Sido Mulyo, Kuta Makmur, North Aceh</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Entrance Ticket Price  : Rp 2,000</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Parking Ticket Price    : Rp 5,000 (motorcycle) Rp 10,000 (car)</span></p>', '', -2, 14, '2017-09-29 07:08:11', 959, '', '2017-09-29 07:08:11', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2017-09-29 07:08:11', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 1, 31, '', '', 1, 1, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', ''),
(30, 358, 'Gunongan', 'gunongan', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Gunongan</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Gunongan had built by Sultan Iskandar Muda (1607-1636) as a private playground and bathing place for his empress Putro Phang (From Malaysia). This whimsical architectural fantasy had access to the sultan''s palace through the traditional the door of Aceh or <em>Pintu Aceh </em>used by royal family only. This building likely functioned as an important recreational place  located in Taman Sari Park for the Queen and other royal family members. It is quite enjoyable to visit this place during the late afternoon while enjoying scenic sunset.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Gunongan is a symbol of Sultan Iskandar Muda’s historical power of love to his empress named Putri Kamaliah also known as Phang Putroe. His empress came from Pahang, Malaysia. The objective of Gunongan (a miniature hills) was to be a recreational place whenever Phang Putroe longed for her homeland in Malaysia.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">The Gunongan edifice is not too big, shingle, shaped like a flower and three-story with its main level a crown of poles that stands upright. On the wall is a low-key entrance that is always locked. From the hallway, there is a ladder leading up to the third level of Gunongan. There is a building called <em>the Cage of the Majesty </em>next to Gunongan. <em>The Cage of the Majesty</em> is the burial site of the Sultan of Aceh and royal family, one of the tomb was a foster son of Sultan Iskandar Muda, Sultan Iskandar Tsani (1636-1641) from Malaysia.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Additional Information:</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Location : </span><br /><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> Taman Sari Gunongan, Seutui Village, Kotamadya Banda Aceh, Nanggroe Aceh  Darussalam, Indonesia.</span></li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Transportation :</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Transportation Access is very easy to find to this location due to Seutui Village is locate in the center of Banda Aceh. Entourage of tourists can enter the location through a gateway located on Teuku Umar Street. Many public transport passing through this location, such as taxi, engine rickshaws and <em>labi-labi </em>(Aceh’s traditional public transport). <em>Labi-labi</em>’s Taman Sari Gunongan route is predominantly passing through Lhoknga - Pasar Aceh, Lamteumen - Pasar Aceh, and Lamlagang - Pasar Aceh.</span></p>', '', -2, 14, '2017-09-29 07:10:02', 959, '', '2017-09-29 07:10:02', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2017-09-29 07:10:02', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 1, 30, '', '', 1, 1, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', ''),
(31, 359, 'Iboih Recreational Forest ', 'iboih-recreational-forest', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Iboih Recreational Forest  </strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Iboih Recreational Forest is renowned for a small yet friendly village. Its people are very hospitable so that foreign visitors easily mingle. Iboih Recreational Forest is situated adjacent to Rubiah Sea Garden. This forest covers about 1300 hectares area and is also protected as a special nature reserve for Weh Island. It is a dense tropical rain forest, although it is difficult to wander trough, the visitors are encouraged to explore it. This area is as home for many kinds of animals for instance wild monkeys, small and big reptiles and colorful birds, the Nicobar pigeon which is not found in any other part of the Indonesian archipelago. At dusk wild boars and swarms of giant fruit bastes are sure sighting which the road ends is a great lookout over the Indian Ocean. It is possible to enjoy a beautiful sunset from Iboh recreational Forest. Despite the big trees, the forest offers some good spots to witness the sunset and enjoy the scenery. In this case, tourists should come in the afternoon before dusk if they do not want to miss such stunning view of the nature. Another popular activity is to enjoy local’s specialty which is Octopus Satay.</span></p>', '', -2, 14, '2017-09-29 07:12:10', 959, '', '2017-09-29 07:12:10', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2017-09-29 07:12:10', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 1, 29, '', '', 1, 2, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', ''),
(32, 360, 'Indra Patra Fortress', 'indra-patra-fortress', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Indra Patra Fortress</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Indra Patra Fortress is renowned for Aceh historical heritage built by the Royal Lamuri, the first Hindu kingdom before the arrival of Islam in Aceh, around seventh century AD. During the reign of Sultan Iskandar Muda, the fort was built in a strategic position for dealing directly with the waterway, thus serving as a bastion of the Portuguese fleet attacks . During the reign of Sultan Iskandar Muda, under the command of Admiral Malahayati, the first female admiral in the world, the fort was used for a defence of Aceh Darussalam kingdom.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">The fort edifice has large and robust construction in a  unique architecture that made of limestone concrete.  Currently, the only remaining of its edifice is the bastion number two which was the door fort that destroyed by the tsunami. Formerly, there were three major parts remaining fortress. The largest fortress measuring 70 x 70 meters with a height of 3 meters, a large and sturdy room measuring 35 x 35 meters and 4 meters high. Its classical design was very special and sophisticated. Many historians  said that the only way to reach the inside of the castle was by climbing.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">In addition, There are two <em>stupas </em>or a building that takes after an arch where the inside or under the vault found wells or water sources in the main fortress that utilized by Hindus for ablutions as a part of the religion service arrangement at that time. There is likewise a dugout inside the stronghold for putting away weapons and dugouts to spare slugs and firearms.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Additional Information</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Location           :  On Krueng Raya Street, Baet, Baitussalam, Kabupaten Aceh Besar, Aceh</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Open               : Everyday at 08.00 am to 06.00 pm</span></p>', '', -2, 14, '2017-09-29 07:13:47', 959, '', '2017-09-29 07:13:47', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2017-09-29 07:13:47', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 1, 28, '', '', 1, 1, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', ''),
(33, 361, 'Lake Laut Tawar', 'lake-laut-tawar', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Lake Laut Tawar </strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Lake Laut Tawar has breathtaking view in a legendary folklore is a-must-visit natural attraction in Aceh. It is located at Gayo Highlands, Central Aceh District, Aceh. The area of the lake is approximately 5,472 hectares, with a length of 17 km and a width of 3.219 km. The volume of water is approximately 2,537,483,884 m³ (2.5 billion liters). The name of <em>Laut Tawar</em> or Fresh Sea derives from the vast area of this lake which has fresh water in it.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">A perfect combination of terrain, hills and waters around Lake Laut Tawar presents prestine natural beauty. We can also see the daily activities of the Gayo highland community around the lake such  as farming, fishing, gardening, plantation pest hunting. The color of the grasses of the hills also varies in other seasons, sometimes the yellowish or greenish that deliver different nuance in every visit of the tourists. The tourists can slurp aceh coffee which is renowned for the best arabica coffee in the world  while enjoying a serene and calming atmosphere. In addition, the sunny weather with blue sky also spoil the photographers with many beautiful photo spots around the lake.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">The panorama around the lake that flanked by two hills presents the beauty of its own for those who visit this place. This lake also has a fish species that only exists here such <em>Depik </em>or <em>Rasbora Tawarensis</em>. It has a fish with slender body as big as human thumb shape, and is sparkling white flaky with savory taste.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">According to folklore, Lake Laut Tawar  wa a result of the story of a princess who married a man from another kingdom, which was not blessed by her parents. When she left the palace, she turned her face backward and it made thunder, lightning and heavy rain that made the princess fell and cried. The rain and the tears of the princess then believed to be the source of the lake.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Additional information</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Location          : West Takengon, Lut Tawar, Central Aceh</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Ticket price      : free of charge</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Place to stay    : there many inns available in Takengon City or  homestays around the lake</span></p>', '', -2, 14, '2017-09-29 07:15:02', 959, '', '2017-09-29 07:15:02', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2017-09-29 07:15:02', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 1, 27, '', '', 1, 1, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', ''),
(34, 362, 'Mount Leuser National Park', 'mount-leuser-national-park', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Mount Leuser National Park</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Mount Leuser National Park  (3,154 m) is the UNESCO World Heritage site of ''The Tropical Rainforest Heritage of Sumatra'' covering an area of 1,094,692 hectares. It represents several ecosystem types, from coastal forest ecosystem through tropical lowland forest ecosystem to montane forest ecosystem. Most of Gunung Leuser National Park area is covered with thick Dipterocarpaceae forest with rivers and waterfalls flowing through it. There are some endangered and peculiar plants, namely daun payung raksasa (Johannesteijsmannia altifrons), rafflesia flowers (Rafflesia atjehensis and R. micropylora), and Rhizanthes zippelnii-the biggest flower, with a diameter of 1.5 metres. In addition, there is one plant unique to the area: the ara, a strangling plant. The area is located under two provincial administration of Aceh and North Sumatra. This park is dominant in East Aceh, South Aceh and Langkat North Sumatra. Most of Gunung Leuser National Park area is covered with thick Dipterocarpaceae forest with rivers and waterfalls flowing through it. There are some endangered and peculiar plants, namely daun payung raksasa (Johannesteijsmannia altifrons), rafflesia flowers (Rafflesia atjehensis and R. micropylora), and Rhizanthes zippelnii-the biggest flower, with a diameter of 1.5 metres. In addition, there is one plant unique to the area: the ara, a strangling plant.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">There are approximately 130 species can be identified in Gunung Leuser National Park, namely: Sumatran tigers, elephants, rhinos, gibbons, monkeys, leopards, reptiles, fish, and 325 species of birds. Endangered and protected animal species which inhabit the Gunung Leuser National Park include orangutan (Pongo abelii), siamang (Hylobates syndactylus syndactylus), Asian elephant (Elephas maximus sumatranus), Sumatran tiger (Panthera tigris sumatrae), Sumatran rhinoceros (Dicerorhinus sumatrensis sumatrensis), serow (Capricornis sumatraensis), great hornbill (Buceros bicornis), sambar deer (Cervus unicolor), and leopard cat (Prionailurus bengalensis sumatrana). Mount Leuser forest also has a rich  of tropical fruits such as mango, rambutan, durian, avocado, orange, papaya, and guava.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">In addition, Mount Leuser National Park includes native ecosystems from the coast to the high mountains which are covered with tropical rain dense forests. The park is administered by a  zoning system for the purpose of research, science, education, cultivation support, tourism, and recreation.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Additional Information</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Declared                     : Minister of Agriculture, in 1980, a total area of 792,675 hectares</span><br /><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> Designated                  : Minister of Forestry, SK. No.276/Kpts-VI/1997, a total area of 1,094,692 </span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">hectares</span><br /><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> Location                      : Regencies Southeast Aceh, South Aceh, Aceh Singkil (Province of </span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Nanggroe  Aceh Darusslam), and Regency of Langkat (Province of</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> North Sumatra)</span><br /><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> Temperature                : 21° - 28° C</span><br /><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> Rainfall                        : 2,000 - 3,200 mm per year</span><br /><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> Altitude                        :  0 - 3,381 meters above sea level</span><br /><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> Best time to visit           :  June to October</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Park Office:                  :  on Raya Blangkejeren Street No. 37 Km 3 PO Box 16, Kutacane, Aceh</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Phone                          : +62-629- 21358</span><br /><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> Fax                              :  +62-629- 21016</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Intriguing Attraction in Mount Leuser National Park</strong></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Gurah offers fantastic scenic, valleys, waterfalls. animals and plants such as Rafflesia, orangutans, birds, snakes and butterflies.</span></li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Bohorok offers an orangutan rehabilitation centre, ecotourism activities like <em>kayaking</em> or canoeing, camping, and birdwatching.</span></li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Kluet offers boating on rivers and lakes, trekking through coastal forest and caving. Kluet is also a habitat of tigers.</span></li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Sekundur offers camping, caving, animal observation.</span></li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Ketambe and Suak Belimbing is a suitable place for research on primates and another rare animals. It has research facilities include accommodation and a library.  For mount climbing enthusiasts also can experience  mountain climbing and hiking as well as river rafting along the Alas River start from Gurah-Muara Situlen-Gelombang for a three-day trip.</span></li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Wildlife Trekking, a wide range of treks into the jungle looking for wildlife are available in Bukit Lawang, Ketembe, Kedah and Tangkahan. There are many tours from 1 to 3 days (sleeping in the jungle) but more or less time can probably be arranged too.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong>Bukit Lawang</strong>, it is highly recommended to do a trek with one of the official rangers from the Orangutan Rehabilitation Centre as there can be problems with guides feeding the orangutans to ensure tourists get a sighting.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong>Ketambe</strong>, entourage of tourists will see real wild living orangutans (not like in Bukit Lawang, were you can even feed them), monkeys and many kind of birds. On a 2 to 3 day trip you can go to a hot spring beside the Alas river and camp over there.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong>Kedah</strong>, entourage of tourists go trekking with Pak Jali (a very experienced, licensed guide, on day walks, one or two nights or for longer treks). Tourists can expect to see orangutans in the wild as well as Black Gibbons, Thomas Leaf Monkeys, Birds and another animals</span></li>\r\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong>Tangkahan</strong>has about 7 elephants and very few tourists. Guides there charge Rp 180,000 for guided jungle treks, furthermore if tourists want to experience rides on the elephants, the price is negotiable. Elephant trekking through the jungle in Tangkahan basically to promote environmental education for visitor through participative patrol program.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol style="text-align: justify;" start="7">\r\n<li><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Mountain Trekking</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">These are all multi-day treks.</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong>Gunung Leuser</strong>, the best starting points are the villages near Blangkejeren. The trek from Kedahto the Gunung Leuser peak and back takes 10 days in total. Guides charge Rp 350,000 per day each person. Since the trek is about 70% in alpine regions</span></li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong>Gunung Kemiri</strong>, the best starting point is Ketambe.</span></li>\r\n</ul>', '', -2, 14, '2017-09-29 07:19:35', 959, '', '2017-09-29 07:19:35', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2017-09-29 07:19:35', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 1, 26, '', '', 1, 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', '');
