(44, 372, 'Glen Labuhan beach Guest House (Monkey beach)', 'glen-labuhan-beach-guest-house-monkey-beach', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Glen Labuhan beach Guest House (Monkey beach)</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Glen Labuhan beach Guest House (Monkey beach) is situated between two jungle covered mountains comprising a sheltered 120 m length of beach, with dense rain forest and lake immediately behind. Some 80 % of the bay is coral rock, the home of uncountable tropical fish. The Northern end of the beach is sand, suitable for swimming out and snorkeling behind the coral. The beach has long been favorite picnic site of expatriates working in parts of Sumatra. The Guest House is on the Beach (within 15 meters of high water line), and overlooks the shoreline trees to islands of Northern tip of Sumatra. It is a first class private Guesthouse with family accommodations in a tropical paradise. Alternative accommodation (for Tarzan enthusiasts) is tree house, some few meters a long beach. All meals are inclusive.</span></p>', '', -2, 14, '2017-09-29 07:42:38', 959, '', '2017-09-29 07:42:38', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2017-09-29 07:42:38', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 1, 16, '', '', 1, 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', ''),
(45, 373, 'The Great Mosque of Aceh (Baiturrahman Grand Mosque)', 'the-great-mosque-of-aceh-baiturrahman-grand-mosque', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>The Great Mosque of Aceh (Baiturrahman Grand Mosque)</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Aceh Province is dubbed into <em>Bumi Serambi Mekkah </em>or Terrace of Mekkah. The great mosque is Aceh’s prominent signature that symbolize religion, culture, spirit and struggle. It is located at the heart of Banda Aceh, Nanggroe Aceh Darusallam. The majestic of the Great Mosque is when world’s worst tsunami wave hit Aceh in 2004, but this mosque can hold the storm and stand still.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">The original Baiturrahman Grand Mosque was built in 1612 during the reign of Sultan Iskandar Muda. Some say the original mosque was built even earlier in 1292 by Sultan Alaidin Mahmudsyah. The original royal mosque featured a multi-tiered thatched roof, a typical feature of Acehnese architecture. When the Colonial administration of the Dutch East Indies attacked the Kraton During the First Aceh Expedition on  April 10<sup>th</sup> of 1873, the Acehnese attacked the KNIL from the Baiturrahman Grand Mosque. From some flares shot onto the thatched roof, the mosque caught fire. General van Swieten promised the local rulers he would rebuild the mosque and create a warm place for mercy. In 1879 the Dutch rebuilt the Mosque Baiturrahman as a gift to and to reduce the anger of the Acehnese people. Construction only began in 1879, when the first stone was laid by Tengku Qadhi Malikul Adil, who became its first imam, and was completed on  December 27<sup>th</sup> of  1881 during the reign of Muhammad Daud Syah, the last sultan of Aceh.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">The Great Mosque is originally designed by the Dutch architect Gerrit Bruins.The design is subsequently adapted by L.P. Luijks, who also supervised the construction work by contractor Lie A Sie. The chosen acrhiterture design was Mughal revival style, characterized by grand domes and minarets.  In addition, The unique black domes are constructed from hard wood shingles combined as tiles. The interior is decorated with relieved wall and pillars, marble staircase and floor from China, stained-glass windows from Belgium, well-decorated wooden doors, and ornate bronze chandeliers. The building stones are from the Netherlands. At the time of its completion, this new design presented a stark contrast compared with the original mosque that many Acehnese refused to pray in the mosque, because it was built by the Dutch "infidels". However, the mosque becomes the pride of  Acehnese people and currently has 7 domes, 8 minarets, and 32 pillars.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Style must get along with local custom</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">To enter this mosque, entourage of tourist must obey the rules that have been set by the board of the mosque. One of them is the dress code in the area or yard of the mosque. All visitors of Baiturrahman  Grand Mosque, the tourists are required to wear Islamic clothes.  Both females and males must cover the<em> aurat </em>(particular body that must not be seen publicly according to Islamic teachings) and should not be dressed tight. For non-Muslims, the great mosque management usually provide a special clothing counter on the Nrth side of the mosque entrance. The tourists also can buy directly Muslim clothes that fit the norm around the Mosque Baiturrahman, in Aceh Market nearby.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Additional Information</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Open               : Publicly open 24/7</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Mosque ID      : 01.1.01.19.01.000001</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Altitude           : 35 m</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Land Area       : 31,000 m<sup>2</sup></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Building Area : 4,000 m<sup>2</sup></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Capacity          : 13,000 people</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Facilities          : Mosque and Yard for congregational prayers, Park, Library. Ablution (<em>Wudhu)                             <br /> </em>Area, Restrooms, Parking Area, Lockers for shoes, and many prayers amenities.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Main Activity  : Pemberdayaan <em>Zakat</em>, <em>Infaq</em>, <em>Shodaqoh</em> and <em>Wakaf</em>, Social Economic Activity </span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">(Mosque Cooperation), Regular Islamic Teachings, Daily Five Congregational Prayers, Friday Congregational Prayers, Islamic Events such <em>Tabligh Akbar, Dakwah Islam, Isra Mi’raj, Maulid Nabi </em>and many more, <em>Buka Puasa Bersama</em> ( Big Breakfasting) during the holy month Ramadhan<em>, Musbaqah Tilawatil Quran </em>or MTQ (Islamic Science Olympiad).</span></p>', '', -2, 14, '2017-09-29 07:46:19', 959, '', '2017-09-29 07:46:19', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2017-09-29 07:46:19', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 1, 15, '', '', 1, 1, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', ''),
(46, 374, 'Cakra Donya Bell', 'cakra-donya-bell', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Cakra Donya Bell</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Admiral Cheng Ho has visited the archipelago in Indonesia for seven times. When he went to Samudera Pasai in 1414 AD, in his fourth goodwill, he gave the giant bell called <em>Cakradonya </em>as a gift from Emperor Yongle, the Chinese ruler, to the Sultan of Samudra Pasai. The bells have been a symbol of the friendship of Aceh and China since the 15<sup>th</sup> century. Currently, the bells are well kept in Banda Aceh Museum. This giant bell has <em>stupa </em>shape, made in 1409 AD. The height reached 125 centimeters, 75 centimeters width. On the outside is engraved the decoration and the Arabic script as well as Chinese script.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">When the Kingdom of Pasai fell in the hands of the Kingdom of Aceh Darussalam led by Sultan Ali Mughayatsyah in 1542 AD, the bell was confiscated and brought to Koetaradja (now Banda Aceh), the center of the Kingdom of Aceh Darussalam. During the reign of Sultan Iskandar Muda (1607-1636), this bell was installed in the stern of a warship named <em>Cakradonya.</em></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">After not being used on the ship, <em>Cakradonya</em> bells had hung in front of the Great Mosque of Banda Aceh or  Baiturrahman Mosque. This bell is often rung when the palace residents had to gather to hear the sultan''s information. Only in 1915, from the Great Mosque, the bell was then moved to the Museum of Aceh until currently.</span></p>', '', -2, 14, '2017-09-29 07:48:24', 959, '', '2017-09-29 07:48:24', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2017-09-29 07:48:24', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 1, 14, '', '', 1, 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', ''),
(47, 375, 'Masjid Raya Baiturrahman or The Great Mosque of Banda Aceh', 'masjid-raya-baiturrahman-or-the-great-mosque-of-banda-aceh', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Masjid Raya Baiturrahman or The Great Mosque of Banda Aceh </strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Baiturrahman is a great mosque located at the centre of Banda Aceh, The mosque has five black coloured domes and four white minarets. The mosque stands upon an elegantly green landscape. The white washed walls and minerals and charcoal blacks domes of the Grand Mosque are the most famous landmark in Aceh. The Mosque was built in 12<sup>th</sup> Century and caught fire several time including during a Dutch attack upon Kutaraja (Banda Aceh) in 1873. A restoration mosque was built by the Dutch military government and was completed in 1883. The Mosque is extraordinary in architecture and ornamentation. It has five onion shaped domes, two tall minarets, wide white walls and decoratively ornamented pillars. Entourage of tourists are encouraged to follow strict dresscodes for budding worshippers and visitors.</span></p>', '', -2, 14, '2017-09-29 07:49:46', 959, '', '2017-09-29 07:49:46', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2017-09-29 07:49:46', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 1, 13, '', '', 1, 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', ''),
(48, 376, 'Cut Nyak Dien House', 'cut-nyak-dien-house', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Cut Nyak Dien House</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Cut Nya Dien was an Indonesian woman revolutionist from Aceh. The house is a replica of the heroine Cut Nyak Dhien House from the Aceh War. The colonial forces burned down the house but a replica was built later. This house in Lam Pisang Village, Lhok Nga Subdistrict about 6 km from Banda Aceh and is currently a museum.  Although Lhok Nga was worst area hit by tsunami, the Cut Nyak Dien House survived. As daughter of a chieftain, Tjut Nyak Dhien joined the fight against the Dutch Colonials in 1875. Her first husband fell in battle, and she remarried. When her second husband also died fighting, she continued the struggle with her children. After six years in the jungle, she was seized by the Dutch and exiled to West Java where she passed away in 1906. Tjut Nyak Dhien is recognised as one of the National Heroine of Indonesia.</span></p>', '', -2, 14, '2017-09-29 07:50:31', 959, '', '2017-09-29 07:50:31', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2017-09-29 07:50:31', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"",