(49, 377, 'Gunongan and Taman Putroe Phang', 'gunongan-and-taman-putroe-phang', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Gunongan and Taman Putroe Phang</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Gunongan had built by Sultan Iskandar Muda (1607-1636) as a private playground and bathing place for Putroe Phang, the empress of Sultan Iskandar Muda (1607-1636) who made him fall in love when the Sultan and his troops succeeded in conquering the Kingdom of Johor and the Kingdom of Pahang in North Malay Peninsula (Malaya). Gunongan also witnessed the love of Sultan to the empress as the place to play when his empress longed for her homeland in Pahang. In the past, Gunongan was also known as <em>Ghairah </em>Park which was swept with the river of Darul Asyiqi (Isyqi), and there was also a cemetery which became the burial place of Sultan Iskandar Tsani (the son-in-law of Sultan Iskandar Muda) formerly used as a lunch place for the King and his Empress as well as the royal family. This whimsical architectural fantasy had access to the sultan''s palace through the traditional <em>Pintu Aceh </em>(the door of Aceh), passed by royal family only. This building likely functioned as an important recreational place located in Taman Sari Park for the Queen and other royal family members. It is quite enjoyable to visit this place during the late afternoon or sunset. </span></p>', '', -2, 14, '2017-09-29 07:53:14', 959, '', '2017-09-29 07:53:14', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2017-09-29 07:53:14', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 1, 11, '', '', 1, 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', ''),
(50, 378, 'Graveyard in Bitay Village', 'graveyard-in-bitay-village', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Graveyard in Bitay Village</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Bitay Village is renowned for a saint graveyard. The tomb of <em>Teuku </em>in Bitay, who taught Achehnese among other things such  the art of casting cannon. The mosque stands beside the grave are regarded as a sacred place until currently. Aceh and Turkey had a close relations in the past. Many technicians and weapons from Turkey came and settled in Aceh. Therefore, a mosque, monument and headstone of Turkish people are found in Bitay Billage that 3 kilometers away from Banda Aceh.</span></p>', '', -2, 14, '2017-09-29 07:55:32', 959, '', '2017-09-29 07:55:32', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2017-09-29 07:55:32', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 1, 10, '', '', 1, 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 0, '*', ''),
(51, 379, 'Aceh Museum', 'aceh-museum', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Aceh Museum</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">The museum is located on Sultan Alaidin Mahmud Syah Street. The museum exhibits ceramics, weapons and many cultural artifacts such as clothing, jewellery, calligraphy, Islamic ornamenation, kitchen equipment and many other items.  The most interesting item is a big bell called “Lonceng Cakra Donya” a gift from China Grand-Duke (Ming Emperor, in the 15<sup>th</sup> century) for Sultan Aceh that was delivered by a Chinese Moslem, Admiral Cheng Ho in 1414, an inscription on the bell “<em>Sing Fang Niat Toeng Juut Kat</em>”. In this museum, there is also ‘<em>Rumah Aceh’</em> or Aceh Traditional House that was built by Dutch Governor Van Swart in 1941. It has currently classic Aceh traditional house architecture. In addition, there is a graveyard complex of the sultans of Aceh in the West area of museum.</span></p>', '', -2, 14, '2017-09-29 07:56:02', 959, '', '2017-09-29 07:56:02', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2017-09-29 07:56:02', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"