(2, 'com_content.article', 'Alif Stone Park and The Mystery of Megalithic Stones', 'alif-stone-park-and-the-mystery-of-megalithic-stones', '<p>Alif Stone Park is a flawless combination of beautiful white sandy beach and blue sea water as well as archaeological elements in Natuna Islands.  Alif Stone Park will also carry the tourists to ancient nuances with hundreds of megalithic giant stones. This rocky park is located on the shore of Sepempang Village, East Bunguran District, Natuna Regency, Riau Islands Province.</p>\r\n<p>Hundreds of boulders in the coastal park has become a mystery for the community of Natuna Regency until currently. This is due to a superficial question, how can the giant rocks put on the beach with an area of ​​approximately 3 hectares. The name Alif Stone Park is taken from one of the stones contained in the area stood upright on another stone like a letter of  <em>Alif</em>  (Arabic Letter). Therefore, the area is called by the people of Alif Stone Park</p>\r\n<p>In Alif Stone Park, there is a small bridge that connects each stone. When you first come to this place, you will pass the crevices of stone with a width of 1 meter, just walk about 10 metres, you will find the entrance of a large stone. After passing through the entrance, the expanse of rocks will appear everywhere along the coast. In some large boulders, there is a small bridge to pass, this allows you to move from one stone to another stone. For those who like to take pictures, there are many picturesque places that can be used as a background for selfie.</p>\r\n<p>Facilities:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Seaview</li>\r\n<li>Homestay</li>\r\n<li>Picturesque Sea Swing</li>\r\n<li><em>Kerangka Paus</em></li>\r\n<li>Alif Stone</li>\r\n<li>Mini Gazebo on Megalithic Stone</li>\r\n<li></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h2>How to get there</h2>\r\n<p>Entourage of tourists can depart from Tanjung Pinang Seaport to Natuna Seaport by ferry. It will take approximately a half day. After reaching Ranai, it only takes about 10-15 minutes to Alif Stone Park.  </p>', -2, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1, '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 957, '', '2017-09-29 04:26:34', 0, '2017-09-29 04:26:34', '*', '2017-09-29 04:26:34', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 22, 347, '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', 0, 1, 0, '', '', 28, '', 1),
(3, 'com_content.article', 'Ex Vietnamese Refugee Camp in Galang Island', 'ex-vietnamese-refugee-camp-in-galang-island', '<p>The Vietnamese Refugee camp in Galang Island, Batam is a historical place that once inhabited by about <strong>250,000 refugees</strong> from Vietnam in <strong>1979-1996</strong>. The camp was built by the UNHCR (United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees), one of the organizations under the United Nations that took care of victims of war, and the government of Indonesia. This refugee camp lies on an area of about 80 hectares. Just like a new ''city'', this camp was equipped with various facilities, ranging from schools, places of worship (churches, temples, and mosque), hospitals, cemeteries, canteens, barracks, and even a prison. </p>\r\n<p>Galang Island has 80 km<sup>2</sup>  width located 40 km away from  Southeast of Batam. It belongs to a group of three islands called Barelang (an abbreviation of Batam-Rempang-Galang). This island is also part of the Riau Islands Province, Indonesia. The nearest city to Galang is Tanjung Pinang in Bintan, about a 30 minute by boat ride. The island is connected by the Barelang Bridge to Rempang and Batam.</p>\r\n<p>Many Vietnamese Boat People and asylum seekers were temporarily accommodated in the Galang camp during the determination of their refugee status and their subsequent resettlement in the USA, Australia and some European Countries. Many Vietnamese from their new resettled countries have come back to visit Galang. For Vietnamese former refugees, especially those who left family members in the disturbingly large cemetery there, or those who lost them at sea on the way to Indonesia, Galang Island has become a kind of pilgrimage site. There are number of visitors that mostly coming from Singapore, also passes through the island, which receives about 1200 guests per month. The local business association, including some former camp officials, were quick to grasp the opportunity to encourage refugee visitors and other tourists to come to the island. Many relics of Vietnamese are still can be seen here. One of those relics are the boat that being used by the Vietnamese refugees to left the country and to avoid a civil war, to this island.</p>\r\n<p>Today, several camp facilities are functioning properly such as Quan Am Tu Pagoda, Chua Kim Quan Pagoda, and the Catholic Church Nha Tho Duc Me Vo Nhiem. These places of worship are still used by visitors who want to worship and pray in the camp area. Two wooden ships that were used by the refugees are also displayed here, near the <strong>Museum of Vietnamese Refugee Camp</strong><strong>, </strong>Galang Island. The museum displays some relics of the refugees, such as ID cards, photos, handcrafts (painting, tablecloth, miniature houses, and many more. Right in front of the museum, lies an Indonesian police office (<em>defunct</em>) and a jail that once used to imprison Vietnamese refugees who committed crimes, such as robbery, escaped from the camp, making liquor, and so on. There is also a Humanity Statue that is located next to the Quan Am Tu Pagoda. The statue was built to commemorate Tinh Nhan, a Vietnamese refugee woman who commited suicide after being raped by a fellow refugee. Not far from the Humanity Statue, there is the Ngha Trang Grave, where more than 500 refugees were buried. Today, the relatives of the people who buried here often visit the complex, as well as the former refugees themselves, who now live in many countries, such as the United States, Australia, the Netherlands, Singapore, etc.</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Additional Information</strong></h2>\r\n<table width="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="21%">\r\n<p><strong>Location</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>:</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>around 50 kilometers from Batam downtown, Sijantung Village, Galang Baru Island</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="21%">\r\n<p><strong>Operating hours</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>:</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p> Weekdays, 7:30am-4:30pm<br />  Weekend, 7:30am-5pm</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="21%">\r\n<p><strong>Entrance fee</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>:</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p> Rp. 3,000/person<br />  Rp. 5,000/motorcycle, Rp. 10,000/car<br />  Rp. 30,000/mini bus<br />  Rp. 50,000/tourist bus</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="21%">\r\n<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>:</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p> Mosque<br />  Church<br />  Temple<br />  Canteen<br />  Toilets<br />  English tourist guide (free)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="21%">\r\n<p><strong>Nearby facilities</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>:</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p> Warungs<br />  Mini shop<br />  Salon</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="21%">\r\n<p><strong>Nearby attractions</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>:</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><a href="http://www.jotravelguide.com/batam_indonesia/melur_beach.php">Melur Beach</a></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="21%">\r\n<p><strong>How to get there</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>:</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>By private car or taxi. It takes less than 1 hour from Batam Centre. If you come by taxi, make sure you ask the driver to wait for you (which should already be communicated way before you take it in downtown Batam).</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="21%"> </td>\r\n<td> </td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p> While exploring the camp by car/motorcycle/bus, please be careful of monkeys along the road<br />  Remove your shoes or slippers before entering temples and mosques<br />  Prohibited from taking photos inside the monastery<br />  For a group visit or to have a guided tour, prior notification is required, minimum 1 week prior to the date of arrival.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p> </p>', -2, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1, '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 957, '', '2017-09-29 04:34:19', 957, '2017-09-29 04:39:10', '*', '2017-09-29 04:34:19', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 25, 351, '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', 0, 3, 0, '', '', 28, '', 1),
(4, 'com_content.article', 'Batam Dragon Fruit Agro Tourism', 'batam-dragon-fruit-agro-tourism', '<p>Batam Dragon Fruit Agro Tourism becomes an intriguing alternative choice for holiday makers particularly to those who have been mundane with  daily routine. Visiting Batam without tasting fresh pick dragon fruit will probably be considered an incomplete visit. This fruit becomes one of the typical fruits of Batam City. Along the Trans Barelang road, particularly around Rempang and Galang, there are dragon fruit plantation. Two prominent farms are Naga Zore and Dragon Fruit Orchards. Naga Zone has an area of approximately 4 hectares.  While. Dragon Fruit Orchards in this region is covering an area of 105 acres are managed by 36 farmers scattered in several locations. The background scenery of its dragon fruit farm is exquisite sea. Entourage of tourists can relax at the cafe in farm area enjoying fresh dragon fruit juice, dragon fruit soup, dragon fruit sticks and so forth in a blue sea panoramic which is decorated behind the dragon fruit plantation.</p>\r\n<p>In addition to directly feel the fresh of dragon fruit juice, tourists can also pick directly from the tree. If you want to pluck straight from the tree must order before Friday owing to the farmers will harvest every Friday to stock up on Saturday and Sunday. The dragon fruit is sold at Rp 40,000 per kilogram which is cheaper than in any supermarket.</p>\r\n<h2><strong>The Story of Dragon Fruit</strong></h2>\r\n<p>Dragon fruit is the fruit of several cactus species of the genera Hylocereus and Selenicereus. This fruit comes from Mexico, Central America and South America but is now also cultivated in Asian countries like Taiwan, Vietnam, Philippines, Indonesia and Malaysia. This fruit can also be found in Okinawa, Israel, Northern Australia and southern China. Hylocereus blooms only at night. In United Kingdom, Dragon fruit  is well-known as <em>Pitaya</em>.</p>\r\n<p>In 1870 this plant was brought from Guiana French people to Vietnam as an ornamental plant. By the Vietnamese and Chinese men are considered a blessing. Therefore, the fruit is always placed between two green dragon tail statues above the altar table. Red fruit color stand out among the green dragons. This is the fruit of a habit among the Vietnamese people are much inuenced Chinese culture known as the Thang Loy (dragon fruit). The term Thang Loy then translated in Europe and other countries who speak English as a dragon fruit</p>\r\n<p>In addition to the sweet taste refreshing, dragon fruit is rich in benets. Many people believe this fruit can lower cholesterol and balance blood sugar. There has been no research on the benets of this fruit, but because the origin of species believed to dragon fruit cactus fruit contains vitamin C, beta carotene, calcium, and carbohydrates. Dragon fruit contains high ber as a binder cancer-causing carcinogen and facilitate the digestive process.</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Additional Information</strong></h2>\r\n<table width="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="23%">\r\n<p>Location</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>:</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Rempang Island (after Barelang Bridge IV)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="23%">\r\n<p>Telephone</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>:</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>+62 811 691274, +62819 800007</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="23%">\r\n<p>Opening hours</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>:</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>weekdays, 9am-5pm; weekend and public holidays, 9am-6:30pm</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="23%">\r\n<p>Admission fee</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>:</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>free</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="23%">\r\n<p>Facilities</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>:</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>restaurant, tour guide (only in Bahasa Indonesia)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="23%">\r\n<p>Remarks</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>:</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>you need give them prior notification, at least 2 days before coming. It is usually will be crowded on weekends and public holidays. Since there is no ATMs along Trans Barelang, it might be better to have some cash money with you.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong> </strong></p>\r\n<h2><strong>How to get there</strong></h2>\r\n<p>It is located in the 4<sup>th</sup> Barelang Bridge, precisely three  islands after leaving  the mainland of Batam. There you will see the dragon fruit gardens which extend to the neat. From the downtown (Batam Centre), it will take approximately 50 minutes, depend from where you are departed</p>', -2, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1, '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference":""}', 957, '', '2017-09-29 04:29:51', 0, '2017-09-29 04:37:09', '*', '2017-09-29 04:29:51', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 23, 352, '{"image_intro":"","float_intro":"","image_intro_alt":"","image_intro_caption":"","image_fulltext":"","float_fulltext":"","image_fulltext_alt":"","image_fulltext_caption":""}', '{"urla":false,"urlatext":"","targeta":"","urlb":false,"urlbtext":"","targetb":"","urlc":false,"urlctext":"","targetc":""}', 0, 2, 1, '', '', 28, '', 1),
(5, 'com_content.article', 'Mangkai Island', 'mangkai-island', '<p>Mangkai Island is one of the outermost islands that located in the group of Anambas Islands. This hilly island has white sandy beaches and rocky land. The island is inhabited only by the lighthouse keeper and the Navy. There is also a small Mangkai island in smaller size next to Mangkai Island. Administratively, this islands are part to the area of Keramut village, Jemaja districts, Natuna Regency, Riau Islands province. The island is located in the Natuna Sea and it borders to Malaysia.</p>\r\n<h2><strong>How to get there:</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To access Mangkai Island, we can depart from Batam to Palmatak, which is the capital of Matak Island by small plane. Then, continue by renting a speedboat to Letung, the capital of Jemaja districts. Then, we can rent another medium-sized motorboat to reach Mangkai Island for about 1 hour and 30 minutes.</li>\r\n<li>In addition, the trip can also be reached by ferry which departed from Tanjungpinang. These ferry boats operate every four days, of which KM. Bukit Raya and KM. Lawit. From Tanjungpinang, the ship will directly leave for Letung -Tarempa and Natuna. It will take approximately 8 hours.</li>\r\n</ul>', -2, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 1, '{"article_layout":"","show_title":"","link_titles":"","show_tags":"","show_intro":"","info_block_position":"","info_block_show_title":"","show_category":"","link_category":"","show_parent_category":"","link_parent_category":"","show_associations":"","show_author":"","link_author":"","show_create_date":"","show_modify_date":"","show_publish_date":"","show_item_navigation":"","show_icons":"","show_print_icon":"","show_email_icon":"","show_vote":"","show_hits":"","show_noauth":"","urls_position":"","alternative_readmore":"","article_page_title":"","show_publishing_options":"","show_article_options":"","show_urls_images_backend":"","show_urls_images_frontend":""}', 0, '{"robots":"","author":"","rights":"","xreference