(435, 22, 1, '', '2017-09-29 04:26:34', 957, 3784, '2407602a87761ceb142596483b4d0c90b3e63d7a', '{"id":22,"asset_id":346,"title":"Alif Stone Park and The Mystery of Megalithic Stones","alias":"alif-stone-park-and-the-mystery-of-megalithic-stones","introtext":"<p>Alif Stone Park is a flawless combination of beautiful white sandy beach and blue sea water as well as archaeological elements in Natuna Islands. \\u00a0Alif Stone Park will also carry the tourists to ancient nuances with hundreds of megalithic giant stones. This rocky park is located on the shore of Sepempang Village, East Bunguran District, Natuna Regency, Riau Islands Province.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Hundreds of boulders in the coastal park has become a mystery for the community of Natuna Regency until currently. This is due to a superficial question, how can the giant rocks put on the beach with an area of \\u200b\\u200bapproximately 3 hectares. The name Alif Stone Park is taken from one of the stones contained in the area stood upright on another stone like a letter of\\u00a0 <em>Alif<\\/em> \\u00a0(Arabic Letter). Therefore, the area is called by the people of Alif Stone Park<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>In Alif Stone Park, there is a small bridge that connects each stone. When you first come to this place, you will pass the crevices of stone with a width of 1 meter, just walk about 10 metres, you will find the entrance of a large stone. After passing through the entrance, the expanse of rocks will appear everywhere along the coast. In some large boulders, there is a small bridge to pass, this allows you to move from one stone to another stone. For those who like to take pictures, there are many picturesque places that can be used as a background for selfie.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Facilities:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n<li>Seaview<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Homestay<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Picturesque Sea Swing<\\/li>\\r\\n<li><em>Kerangka Paus<\\/em><\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Alif Stone<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>Mini Gazebo on Megalithic Stone<\\/li>\\r\\n<li><\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ol>\\r\\n<h2>How to get there<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>Entourage of tourists can depart from Tanjung Pinang Seaport to Natuna Seaport by ferry. It will take approximately a half day. After reaching Ranai, it only takes about 10-15 minutes to Alif Stone Park. \\u00a0<\\/p>","fulltext":"","state":1,"catid":"28","created":"2017-09-29 04:26:34","created_by":"957","created_by_alias":"","modified":"2017-09-29 04:26:34","modified_by":null,"checked_out":null,"checked_out_time":null,"publish_up":"2017-09-29 04:26:34","publish_down":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","images":"{\\"image_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"float_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_caption\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"float_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_caption\\":\\"\\"}","urls":"{\\"urla\\":false,\\"urlatext\\":\\"\\",\\"targeta\\":\\"\\",\\"urlb\\":false,\\"urlbtext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetb\\":\\"\\",\\"urlc\\":false,\\"urlctext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetc\\":\\"\\"}","attribs":"{\\"article_layout\\":\\"\\",\\"show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_titles\\":\\"\\",\\"show_tags\\":\\"\\",\\"show_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_position\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"show_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_associations\\":\\"\\",\\"show_author\\":\\"\\",\\"link_author\\":\\"\\",\\"show_create_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_modify_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publish_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_item_navigation\\":\\"\\",\\"show_icons\\":\\"\\",\\"show_print_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_email_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_vote\\":\\"\\",\\"show_hits\\":\\"\\",\\"show_noauth\\":\\"\\",\\"urls_position\\":\\"\\",\\"alternative_readmore\\":\\"\\",\\"article_page_title\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publishing_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_article_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_backend\\":\\"\\",\\"show_urls_images_frontend\\":\\"\\"}","version":1,"ordering":null,"metakey":"","metadesc":"","access":"1","hits":null,"metadata":"{