(442, 23, 1, '', '2017-09-29 04:37:09', 957, 6412, 'f02cb8890af4b5d6629a8ce7785283b1a40da2cd', '{"id":23,"asset_id":"348","title":"Batam Dragon Fruit Agro Tourism","alias":"batam-dragon-fruit-agro-tourism","introtext":"<p>Batam Dragon Fruit Agro Tourism becomes an intriguing alternative choice for holiday makers particularly to those who have been mundane with\\u00a0 daily routine. Visiting Batam without tasting fresh pick dragon fruit will probably be considered an incomplete visit. This fruit becomes one of the typical fruits of Batam City. Along the Trans Barelang road, particularly around Rempang and Galang, there are dragon fruit plantation. Two prominent farms are Naga Zore and Dragon Fruit Orchards. Naga Zone has an area of approximately 4 hectares. \\u00a0While. Dragon Fruit Orchards in this region is covering an area of 105 acres are managed by 36 farmers scattered in several locations. The background scenery of its dragon fruit farm is exquisite sea. Entourage of tourists can relax at the cafe in farm area enjoying fresh dragon fruit juice, dragon fruit soup, dragon fruit sticks and so forth in a blue sea panoramic which is decorated behind the dragon fruit plantation.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>In addition to directly feel the fresh of dragon fruit juice, tourists can also pick directly from the tree. If you want to pluck straight from the tree must order before Friday owing to the farmers will harvest every Friday to stock up on Saturday and Sunday. The dragon fruit is sold at Rp 40,000 per kilogram which is cheaper than in any supermarket.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2><strong>The Story of Dragon Fruit<\\/strong><\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>Dragon fruit is the fruit of several cactus species of the genera Hylocereus and Selenicereus. This fruit comes from Mexico, Central America and South America but is now also cultivated in Asian countries like Taiwan, Vietnam, Philippines, Indonesia and Malaysia. This fruit can also be found in Okinawa, Israel, Northern Australia and southern China. Hylocereus blooms only at night. In United Kingdom, Dragon fruit\\u00a0 is well-known as <em>Pitaya<\\/em>.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>In 1870 this plant was brought from Guiana French people to Vietnam as an ornamental plant. By the Vietnamese and Chinese men are considered a blessing. Therefore, the fruit is always placed between two green dragon tail statues above the altar table. Red fruit color stand out among the green dragons. This is the fruit of a habit among the Vietnamese people are much inuenced Chinese culture known as the Thang Loy (dragon fruit). The term Thang Loy then translated in Europe and other countries who speak English as a dragon fruit<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>In addition to the sweet taste refreshing, dragon fruit is rich in benets. Many people believe this fruit can lower cholesterol and balance blood sugar. There has been no research on the benets of this fruit, but because the origin of species believed to dragon fruit cactus fruit contains vitamin C, beta carotene, calcium, and carbohydrates. Dragon fruit contains high ber as a binder cancer-causing carcinogen and facilitate the digestive process.<\\/p>\\r\\n<h2><strong>Additional Information<\\/strong><\\/h2>\\r\\n<table width=\\"0\\">\\r\\n<tbody>\\r\\n<tr>\\r\\n<td width=\\"23%\\">\\r\\n<p>Location<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td>\\r\\n<p>:<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td>\\r\\n<p>Rempang Island (after Barelang Bridge IV)<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr>\\r\\n<td width=\\"23%\\">\\r\\n<p>Telephone<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td>\\r\\n<p>:<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td>\\r\\n<p>+62 811 691274, +62819 800007<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr>\\r\\n<td width=\\"23%\\">\\r\\n<p>Opening hours<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td>\\r\\n<p>:<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td>\\r\\n<p>weekdays, 9am-5pm; weekend and public holidays, 9am-6:30pm<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr>\\r\\n<td width=\\"23%\\">\\r\\n<p>Admission fee<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td>\\r\\n<p>:<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td>\\r\\n<p>free<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr>\\r\\n<td width=\\"23%\\">\\r\\n<p>Facilities<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td>\\r\\n<p>:<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td>\\r\\n<p>restaurant, tour guide (only in Bahasa Indonesia)<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr>\\r\\n<tr>\\r\\n<td width=\\"23%\\">\\r\\n<p>Remarks<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td>\\r\\n<p>:<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<td>\\r\\n<p>you need give them prior notification, at least 2 days before coming. It is usually will be crowded on weekends and public holidays. Since there is no ATMs along Trans Barelang, it might be better to have some cash money with you.<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/td>\\r\\n<\\/tr>\\r\\n<\\/tbody>\\r\\n<\\/table>\\r\\n<p><strong>\\u00a0<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n<h2><strong>How to get there<\\/strong><\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>It is located in the 4<sup>th<\\/sup> Barelang Bridge, precisely three \\u00a0islands after leaving \\u00a0the mainland of Batam. There you will see the dragon fruit gardens which extend to the neat. From the downtown (Batam Centre), it will take approximately 50 minutes, depend from where you are departed<\\/p>","fulltext":"","state":1,"catid":"28","created":"2017-09-29 04:29:51","created_by":"957","created_by_alias":"","modified":"2017-09-29 04:37:09","modified_by":"957","checked_out":"957","checked_out_time":"2017-09-29 04:36:31","publish_up":"2017-09-29 04:29:51","publish_down":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","images":"{\\"image_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"float_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_caption\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"float_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_caption\\":\\"\\"}","urls":"{\\"urla\\":false,\\"urlatext\\":\\"\\",\\"targeta\\":\\"\\",\\"urlb\\":false,\\"urlbtext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetb\\":\\"\\",\\"urlc\\":false,\\"urlctext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetc\\":\\"\\"}","attribs":"{\\"article_layout\\":\\"\\",\\"show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_titles\\":\\"\\",\\"show_tags\\":\\"\\",\\"show_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_position\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_show_title\\":\\"\\"