(1073, 62, 1, '', '2017-10-04 14:18:20', 958, 2689, '0d201c37bc50107f16ef75a22345e9f0b5b77684', '{"id":62,"asset_id":"987","title":"ARRIVING BY AIR","alias":"arriving-by-air","introtext":"<p>ARRIVING BY AIR<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Many international airlines offer flights into Indonesia\\u2019s international airports. From there travelers can board connecting flights on a number of local airlines to all major cities throughout the archipelago.<br \\/>Airports.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The three main international airports are Soekarno-Hatta (CGK) at Tangerang, Banten, near Jakarta, Ngurah Rai (DPS) at Denpasar, Bali and Juanda (SUB) at Surabaya, East Java. Many other cities have air links with Singapore, Malaysia and other destinations. These include Hang Nadim International Airport in Batam, Kepulauan Riau, Kualanamu International Airport in Medan, North Sumatra, Sultan Syarif Kasim II International Airport in Pekanbaru, Sultan Mahmud Badaruddin II Airport in Palembang and Adisutjipto International Airport in Yogyakarta.<\\/p>","fulltext":"","state":1,"catid":"209","created":"2017-10-04 08:15:39","created_by":"958","created_by_alias":"","modified":"2017-10-04 14:18:20","modified_by":"958","checked_out":"958","checked_out_time":"2017-10-04 14:17:59","publish_up":"2017-10-04 08:15:39","publish_down":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","images":"{\\"image_intro\\":\\"images\\\\\\/frontpage_images\\\\\\/articles\\\\\\/305. Soekarno-Hatta_Airport_aerial_view.jpg\\",\\"float_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_caption\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"float_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_caption\\":\\"\\"}","urls":"{\\"urla\\":false,\\"urlatext\\":\\"\\",\\"targeta\\":\\"\\",\\"urlb\\":false,\\"urlbtext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetb\\":\\"\\",\\"urlc\\":false,\\"urlctext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetc\\":\\"\\"}","attribs":"{\\"article_layout\\":\\"\\",\\"show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_titles\\":\\"\\",\\"show_tags\\":\\"\\",\\"show_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"info_b