(1426, 61, 1, '', '2017-10-06 03:15:47', 958, 3963, '966fc4ff5df7f9c567c636ba0dda0968d1f9b970', '{"id":61,"asset_id":"831","title":"INTRODUCING INDONESIA","alias":"introducing-indonesia","introtext":"<p>Indonesia is the largest archipelago in the world with 18,000 islands, over 6,000 of them inhabited, straddling the Equator over 5,000 kilometres from Aceh in the west to Papua in the east, that borders Papua New Guinea. It is shares a land border with Malaysia to its north on the island of Borneo and another border with Timor Leste; its former colony.<\\/p>\\r\\n","fulltext":"\\r\\n<p>Based on 2015 census data, by July 2017 Indonesia had a population of just over 260 million people, making it the fourth most populous country in the world after China, India and the USA. It is also the largest Muslim population in the world and, due to its geographic breadth, very ethnically diverse.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Indonesia has some of the largest cities on the planet including the capital Jakarta and major provincial cities such as Surabaya, Bandung, Medan, Semarang and Yogyakarta. There are many other large cities across Indonesia as can be expected from such populous country.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Indonesia, while home to the world-renowned island of Bali, is an otherwise largely untapped source unique tourist experiences. Over 90% of international visitors go to Bali, with only a small percentage venturing beyond its wonderful shores. Tourists that do elsewhere go to nearby Lombok and the Gili Islands or maybe Borobudur, Yogyakarta, Bandung, Jakarta or Komodo to see the dragons. A few more adventurous folk may go to Raja Ampat or Kalimantan to see the Orangutans.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Many international airlines offer flights into Indonesia\\u2019s international airports. From there travelers have a number of options to venture further afield by getting a connecting flight on a number of local airlines to all major cities throughout the archipelago. Other ways to travel include: by train across Java and parts of Sumatra or by island hopping by ferry.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Infrastructure off Java, Bali and outside major cities and towns can be limited, so travelers going to many places will need some patience and flexibility.<\\/p>","state":1,"catid":"206","created":"2017-10-04 05:59:42","created_by":"958","created_by_alias":"","modified":"2017-10-06 03:15:47","modified_by":"958","checked_out":"958","checked_out_time":"2017-10-06 03:15:13","publish_up":"2017-10-04 05:59:42","publish_down":"0000-00-00 00:00:00","images":"{\\"image_intro\\":\\"images\\\\\\/frontpage_images\\\\\\/articles\\\\\\/Jakarta Skyline.jpeg\\",\\"float_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_alt\\":\\"\\",\\"image_intro_caption\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext\\":\\"images\\\\\\/frontpage_images\\\\\\/articles\\\\\\/Jakarta Skyline.jpeg\\",\\"float_fulltext\\":\\"\\",\\"image_fulltext_alt\\":\\"Jakarta Skyline\\",\\"image_fulltext_caption\\":\\"\\"}","urls":"{\\"urla\\":false,\\"urlatext\\":\\"\\",\\"targeta\\":\\"\\",\\"urlb\\":false,\\"urlbtext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetb\\":\\"\\",\\"urlc\\":false,\\"urlctext\\":\\"\\",\\"targetc\\":\\"\\"}","attribs":"{\\"article_layout\\":\\"\\",\\"show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"link_titles\\":\\"\\",\\"show_tags\\":\\"\\",\\"show_intro\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_position\\":\\"\\",\\"info_block_show_title\\":\\"\\",\\"show_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"link_parent_category\\":\\"\\",\\"show_associations\\":\\"\\",\\"show_author\\":\\"\\",\\"link_author\\":\\"\\",\\"show_create_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_modify_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_publish_date\\":\\"\\",\\"show_item_navigation\\":\\"\\",\\"show_icons\\":\\"\\",\\"show_print_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_email_icon\\":\\"\\",\\"show_vote\\":\\"\\",\\"show_hits\\":\\"\\",\\"show_noauth\\":\\"\\",\\"urls_position\\":\\"\\",\\"alternative_readmore\\":\\"Read more...\\",\\"article_page_title\\":\\"Introducing Indonesia\\",\\"show_publishing_options\\":\\"\\",\\"show_article_options\\":\\"\\",\\"sh